---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const meta = {
  title: "SPMO Expense Ratio & Dividend Analysis",
  description: "Does the Invesco S&P 500 Momentum ETF (SPMO) justify its fees? We uncover the exact expense ratio, yield, and 5-year dividend history to find out.",
  category: "study",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": ["Article", "FAQPage"],
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the SPMO expense ratio?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The expense ratio for the Invesco S&P 500 Momentum ETF (SPMO) is 0.13%. This means you pay $13 annually for every $10,000 invested."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Does SPMO pay a dividend?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, SPMO pays a quarterly dividend. Currently, its trailing twelve-month yield is around 1.05%, which translates to an annual payout of roughly $0.92 per share."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How often does SPMO pay dividends?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "SPMO distributes its dividends on a quarterly basis, typically with ex-dividend dates falling in March, June, September, and December."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is the SPMO expense ratio high compared to SPY?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "SPMO's 0.13% expense ratio is slightly higher than SPY (0.09%) and VOO (0.03%). However, for a targeted smart-beta momentum strategy, 0.13% is considered extremely competitive."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the historical dividend growth rate for SPMO?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "SPMO's dividend has grown from roughly $0.50 per share in 2020 to $0.92 per share in 2024. Because it is a momentum ETF, its dividend growth is erratic and depends entirely on the current highest-momentum sectors it holds."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<SiteLayout site="westmount" title={meta.title} description={meta.description} canonical="https://westmountfundamentals.com/spmo-expense-ratio" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>SPMO Expense Ratio & Dividend Analysis</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Evaluating the costs and payouts of the Invesco S&P 500 Momentum ETF.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="content-section">
      <p>The <strong>Invesco S&P 500 Momentum ETF (SPMO)</strong> has gained immense popularity among investors looking to ride the strongest trends within the S&P 500. By tracking an index of the 100 stocks exhibiting the highest momentum scores, SPMO aims to outperform the broader market. But two critical questions remain for long-term investors: does the <strong>SPMO expense ratio</strong> justify its active-like strategy, and what kind of dividend yield can you actually expect?</p>

      <h2>Current Dividend Yield and Payout Profile</h2>
      <p>Unlike standard index funds, SPMO's yield fluctuates wildly depending on the sectors currently exhibiting the highest momentum. In a tech-heavy bull market, its yield drops; when defensive stocks lead, the yield spikes.</p>

      <div class="stats-grid">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <h3>SPMO Expense Ratio</h3>
          <p class="calc-result-value">0.13%</p>
          <span class="badge positive">Low Cost</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <h3>Current Dividend Yield</h3>
          <p class="calc-result-value">1.05%</p>
          <span class="badge neutral">Quarterly Payout</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>Currently, SPMO offers a trailing twelve-month dividend yield of roughly 1.05%. This translates to an annual distribution of approximately $0.92 per share. The ETF pays out dividends on a quarterly schedule, with typical ex-dividend dates falling in the third week of March, June, September, and December.</p>

      <h2>5-Year Dividend History</h2>
      <p>The historical dividend payouts for SPMO showcase a generally upward, albeit somewhat erratic, trajectory. Because the fund reconstitutes its holdings to chase momentum, the underlying dividend-paying stocks within the ETF change drastically from year to year.</p>

      <div class="table-container">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Year</th>
              <th>Annual Dividend (per share)</th>
              <th>YoY Growth</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>2024</td>
              <td>$0.92</td>
              <td>+21.0%</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2023</td>
              <td>$0.76</td>
              <td>+11.7%</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2022</td>
              <td>$0.68</td>
              <td>+17.2%</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2021</td>
              <td>$0.58</td>
              <td>+16.0%</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2020</td>
              <td>$0.50</td>
              <td>N/A</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2>Dividend Growth Rate Analysis</h2>
      <p>Between 2020 and 2024, SPMO's annual dividend payout grew from $0.50 to $0.92. While this represents robust compound growth, it is crucial to understand that this is a byproduct of the fund's momentum strategy rather than a deliberate focus on dividend-growing companies like those found in <a href="/schd-dividend-calculator">SCHD</a> or <a href="/dividend-aristocrats-complete-list-2026">Dividend Aristocrats</a>. If momentum shifts purely to non-dividend-paying growth stocks, SPMO's yield could plummet overnight.</p>

      <h2>Comparison to Category Average</h2>
      <p>At <strong>0.13%</strong>, the SPMO expense ratio is incredibly competitive. You are paying just $13 annually for every $10,000 invested to gain access to a dynamic, smart-beta strategy. For context, the average actively managed equity ETF charges between 0.40% and 0.65%. Even compared to baseline S&P 500 funds like <a href="/spy-expense-ratio-vs-voo">SPY (0.09%)</a> and <a href="/voo-etf-review-2026">VOO (0.03%)</a>, the premium for SPMO's momentum overlay is minimal.</p>

      <h2>Key Metrics and Fundamentals</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Expense Ratio:</strong> 0.13% ($13 per $10k invested).</li>
        <li><strong>AUM:</strong> Multi-billion dollar asset base ensuring high liquidity.</li>
        <li><strong>Sector Breakdown:</strong> Highly dynamic. In recent years, it has heavily favored Information Technology and Communication Services, though it will rotate entirely if those sectors lose momentum.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="calculator-card">
        <h3>SPMO Dividend Reinvestment Calculator</h3>
        <p>Estimate the projected annual income from your SPMO shares based on the trailing $0.92/year payout.</p>

        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="shares">Shares Owned</label>
          <div class="input-wrapper">
            <input type="number" id="shares" value="100" min="1" step="1">
            <span class="suffix">shares</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="dps">Annual Dividend Per Share ($)</label>
          <div class="input-wrapper">
            <input type="number" id="dps" value="0.92" min="0" step="0.01" readonly style="background: var(--bg-color); opacity: 0.7; cursor: not-allowed;">
            <span class="suffix">/ yr</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="calc-result">
          <span class="calc-result-label">Projected Annual Income</span>
          <div class="calc-result-value" id="projectedIncome">$92.00</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <section class="faq-section">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <details>
          <summary>What is the SPMO expense ratio?</summary>
          <p>The expense ratio for the Invesco S&P 500 Momentum ETF (SPMO) is 0.13%. This means you pay $13 annually for every $10,000 invested.</p>
        </details>

        <details>
          <summary>Does SPMO pay a dividend?</summary>
          <p>Yes, SPMO pays a quarterly dividend. Currently, its trailing twelve-month yield is around 1.05%, which translates to an annual payout of roughly $0.92 per share.</p>
        </details>

        <details>
          <summary>How often does SPMO pay dividends?</summary>
          <p>SPMO distributes its dividends on a quarterly basis, typically with ex-dividend dates falling in March, June, September, and December.</p>
        </details>

        <details>
          <summary>Is the SPMO expense ratio high compared to SPY?</summary>
          <p>SPMO's 0.13% expense ratio is slightly higher than SPY (0.09%) and VOO (0.03%). However, for a targeted smart-beta momentum strategy, 0.13% is considered extremely competitive.</p>
        </details>

        <details>
          <summary>What is the historical dividend growth rate for SPMO?</summary>
          <p>SPMO's dividend has grown from roughly $0.50 per share in 2020 to $0.92 per share in 2024. Because it is a momentum ETF, its dividend growth is erratic and depends entirely on the current highest-momentum sectors it holds.</p>
        </details>
      </section>
    </section>
  </div>
  <script is:inline>
    function initSPMOCalculator() {
      const container = document.querySelector('.calculator-card');
      if (!container || container.dataset.initialized === 'true') return;

      const sharesInput = document.getElementById('shares');
      const dpsInput = document.getElementById('dps');
      const projectedIncome = document.getElementById('projectedIncome');

      function updateCalculator() {
        const shares = parseFloat(sharesInput.value) || 0;
        const dps = parseFloat(dpsInput.value) || 0;

        const income = shares * dps;
        projectedIncome.textContent = `$${income.toFixed(2)}`;
      }

      sharesInput.addEventListener('input', updateCalculator);

      container.dataset.initialized = 'true';
    }

    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', initSPMOCalculator);
    document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', initSPMOCalculator);
  </script>
  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .content-section { margin-top: 2rem; }
    .stats-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .stat-card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; text-align: center; }
    .stat-card h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .calc-result-value { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-color); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .badge { display: inline-block; padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; border-radius: 9999px; font-family: var(--font-mono); }
    .badge.positive { background-color: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1); color: #22c55e; }
    .badge.neutral { background-color: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.1); color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .table-container { overflow-x: auto; margin: 2rem 0; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    th, td { padding: 1rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    th { background-color: rgba(74, 143, 231, 0.05); color: var(--accent-color); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 0.85rem; }
    td { color: var(--text-secondary); font-family: var(--font-mono); }
    tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    .calculator-card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2.5rem 0; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); }
    .calculator-card h3 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .calculator-card p { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .input-group { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .input-group label { display: block; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 600; }
    .input-wrapper { position: relative; display: flex; align-items: center; }
    .input-wrapper input { width: 100%; background: var(--bg-color); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-primary); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 1.1rem; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: 8px; }
    .input-wrapper input:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--accent-color); }
    .suffix { position: absolute; right: 1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); font-family: var(--font-mono); pointer-events: none; }
    .calc-result { margin-top: 2rem; padding-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); text-align: center; }
    .calc-result-label { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .faq-section { margin-top: 3rem; }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1.25rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .faq-section details p { margin-top: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
